<item>
            <title>[LU-2025] cd&apos;ing to a certain directory causes client eviction</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2025</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Directory not accessible. When a CD is typed as follows: &lt;br/&gt;
cd /scratch1/portfolios/NCEPDEV/jcsda/noscrub/Yong.Chen/CRTM_ODPStraining/work_ir_v12.1_Zeus/ECMWF83/iasiB3_metop-a &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following error is generated after a ~6 minute wait: &lt;br/&gt;
cannot access iasiB3_metop-a: Cannot send after transport endpoint shutdown &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ls of this directory hangs for more than 10 minutes. behavior is not see on any of the parent directories.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appears that the MDT gets stuck and the client is eventually evicted. I have kernel messages from the the client as well as debug logs for the client and MDT. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
